<p> One way to see that <m>\sqrt{x^2}</m> and <m>x</m> are not equivalent is to compare the graphs of <m>Y_1 = \sqrt{x^2}</m> and <m>Y_2 = x</m>, shown below.  You can see that <m>\sqrt{x^2}</m> and <m>x</m> do not have the same value for <m>x \lt 0</m>.</p>

