 <p>Thus, to check to whether an equation is an identity, we can compare graphs of <m>Y_1 = </m> (left side of the equation) and <m>Y_2 = </m> (right side of the equation).   If the two graphs are identical, the equation is an identity.  If the two graphs are not the same, the equation is not an identity.</p> 





